{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Song of Bengalese finches\n",
    "The song of bengalese finches has beens show to cluster into discrete syllable types, which are recoverable using unsupervised methods. \n",
    "\n",
    "We here closely follow the procedure described in Sainburg et al. (2020): Finding, visualizing, and quantifying latent structure across (see code on [github](https://github.com/timsainb/avgn_paper))."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T08:58:36.671Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T08:58:36.666Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T08:58:41.280Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T08:58:41.302Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import sklearn\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import librosa.feature\n",
    "from matplotlib.colors import ListedColormap, LinearSegmentedColormap\n",
    "import colorcet as cc\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "import das_unsupervised.spec_utils\n",
    "import umap\n",
    "import hdbscan\n",
    "from io import BytesIO\n",
    "import urllib.request\n",
    "from noisereduce.noisereducev1 import reduce_noise\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "%config InlineBackend.figure_format = 'jpg'  # smaller mem footprint for page\n",
    "plt.style.use('ncb.mplstyle')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Download audio data\n",
    "Data of four Bengalese finches from: D Nicholson, JE Queen, S Sober (2017). Bengalese finch song repository. See [data repo](https://doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.4805749.v5]) on figshare."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "url = 'https://github.com/janclemenslab/das_unsupervised/releases/download/v0.4/birds.npz'\n",
    "with urllib.request.urlopen(url) as f:\n",
    "    ff = BytesIO(f.read())\n",
    "\n",
    "d = np.load(ff)\n",
    "recording = d['recording']\n",
    "syllable_onsets = d['syllable_onsets']\n",
    "syllable_offsets = d['syllable_offsets']\n",
    "syllable_types = d['syllable_types']\n",
    "samplerate = d['samplerate']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Pre-processing\n",
    "Noise reduction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "noise_clip = recording[:150_000]\n",
    "x_nr = reduce_noise(audio_clip=recording, noise_clip=noise_clip, verbose=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Compute the spectrogram"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T08:59:16.956Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T08:59:16.947Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T08:59:26.207Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T08:59:26.243Z"
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(128,)\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1440x144 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "hop_length = int(2 * samplerate / 1000)\n",
    "win_length = int(10 * samplerate / 1000 * 2)\n",
    "specgram = librosa.feature.melspectrogram(x_nr, sr=samplerate, n_fft=win_length, hop_length=hop_length, power=2)\n",
    "specgram = specgram[np.where(specgram[:,0]!=0)[0],:]\n",
    "sm = np.median(specgram, axis=1)\n",
    "print(sm.shape)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(20, 2))\n",
    "plt.imshow(np.log2(specgram), cmap='turbo')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Extract and threshold syllables from spectrogram"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:00:13.819Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:00:13.812Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:00:16.312Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:00:16.338Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<function matplotlib.pyplot.show(close=None, block=None)>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 34,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x720 with 32 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "specs = [] \n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))\n",
    "for cnt, (onset, offset) in enumerate(zip(syllable_onsets, syllable_offsets)):\n",
    "    spec = np.log2(specgram[:, int(onset/hop_length):int(offset/hop_length)] / sm[:, np.newaxis])\n",
    "    spec = spec[4:-20:2, :]\n",
    "    spec = spec - 2\n",
    "    spec[spec<0] = 0\n",
    "    specs.append(spec)\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        plt.subplot(4,4,cnt+1)\n",
    "        plt.imshow(specs[-1], cmap='turbo')\n",
    "        plt.xlim(0, 50)\n",
    "        plt.colorbar()\n",
    "    except:\n",
    "        pass\n",
    "plt.show"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Log-scale the time axis to reduce differences in syllable duration and zero-pad all syllables to the same duration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 35,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:00:16.522Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:00:16.518Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:00:17.168Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:00:17.173Z"
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "spec_rs = [das_unsupervised.spec_utils.log_resize_spec(spec, scaling_factor=8) for spec in specs]\n",
    "\n",
    "max_len = np.max([spec.shape[1] for spec in spec_rs])\n",
    "spec_rs = [das_unsupervised.spec_utils.pad_spec(spec, pad_length=max_len) for spec in spec_rs]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Flatten 2D [time x freq] spectrograms to 1D feature vectors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 36,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:00:17.190Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:00:17.183Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:00:17.227Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:00:17.245Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "spec_flat = [spec.ravel() for spec in spec_rs]\n",
    "spec_flat = np.array(spec_flat)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Dimensionality reduction and clustering\n",
    "Embed the feature vectors into a 2D space using [UMAP](https://umap-learn.readthedocs.io/) and cluster the resulting groups of syllables with [hdbscan](https://hdbscan.readthedocs.io/)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 37,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:00:17.239Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:00:17.234Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:00:23.206Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:00:23.229Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "/Users/clemens10/miniconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/sklearn/manifold/_spectral_embedding.py:245: UserWarning: Graph is not fully connected, spectral embedding may not work as expected.\n",
      "  warnings.warn(\"Graph is not fully connected, spectral embedding\"\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "out = umap.UMAP(min_dist=0.5, random_state=2).fit_transform(spec_flat)\n",
    "hdbscan_labels = hdbscan.HDBSCAN(min_samples=10, min_cluster_size=20).fit_predict(out)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Plot results\n",
    "Syllable spectrograms embedded into a 2D space, colored by manual syllable labels (left) and by the unsupervised cluster labels (right). \n",
    "Syllables fall into separate groups, which are consistent with the grouping imposed by manual labelling (left, syllables of the same label are grouped together). The clustering (right) recovers the manual separation by tends to find  more subdivisions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:00:23.223Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:00:23.219Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:00:23.374Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:00:23.397Z"
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x576 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))\n",
    "plt.subplot(121)\n",
    "plt.scatter(out[:,0], out[:,1], c=syllable_types, cmap='cet_glasbey_dark', alpha=0.2, s=8)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('UMAP 1')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('UMAP 2')\n",
    "plt.title('Manual syllable labels')\n",
    "\n",
    "# colormap with cluster label 0 (outliers) grey\n",
    "cmap = cc.palette['glasbey_dark']\n",
    "cmap = list(cmap)\n",
    "cmap.insert(0, (0.7, 0.7, 0.7))\n",
    "cmap = ListedColormap(cmap)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(122)\n",
    "plt.scatter(out[:,0], out[:,1], c=hdbscan_labels, cmap=cmap, alpha=0.2, s=8, edgecolor='none')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('UMAP 1')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('UMAP 2')\n",
    "plt.title('Unsupervised syllable labels')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Confusion matrix to compare manual and cluster syllable labels. Most syllables are assigned a single cluster labels."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:00:23.989Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:00:23.985Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:00:24.067Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:00:24.090Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      " Homogeneity_score: 0.91\n",
      " Completeness_score: 0.96\n",
      " V_measure_score: 0.94\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x360 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "uni, syllable_types_relabeled = np.unique(syllable_types, return_inverse=True)  # remove non-used labels\n",
    "C = sklearn.metrics.confusion_matrix(syllable_types_relabeled, hdbscan_labels, normalize='true')\n",
    "idx = np.argmax(C, axis=0)  # re-order columns\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))\n",
    "plt.imshow(C[idx, :])\n",
    "plt.colorbar()\n",
    "plt.title('Confusion matrix')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Manual label')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Cluster label')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f' Homogeneity_score: {sklearn.metrics.homogeneity_score(syllable_types, hdbscan_labels):1.2f}\\n',\n",
    "      f'Completeness_score: {sklearn.metrics.completeness_score(syllable_types, hdbscan_labels):1.2f}\\n',\n",
    "      f'V_measure_score: {sklearn.metrics.v_measure_score(syllable_types, hdbscan_labels):1.2f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Average spectrograms of the syllables in each cluster reveal the spectral features that discriminat syllables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:00:24.079Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:00:24.074Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:00:25.811Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:00:25.824Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 30 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "  plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "  for label in np.unique(hdbscan_labels):\n",
    "      if label>=0:\n",
    "        idx = np.where(hdbscan_labels==label)[0]\n",
    "        plt.subplot(7, 7, label+1)\n",
    "        plt.imshow(np.mean(np.array(spec_rs)[idx], axis=0), cmap='cet_CET_L17')\n"
   ]
  },
  {
